reviews.text: Great place to go relax and have some fun. The offer food and select drinks. Now serving alcohol. Kinda pricey but to be expected.

RV park located just a stone's throw away from 30 mile bike path that wraps around the lake and a truly beautiful beach with post card like views. Free to walk in. Water in July was super warm. Beach sand is soft with only a few spots that show a bit of gravel. Water is quite shallow anywhere near shore making it kid friendly swimming. 3-5 Lifeguards on duty. Select food and drink available at small concessions area. Alcohol served in small but pleasant tiki patio. Just minutes to downtown Burlington with all of its charm. Many shops and restaurants to visit. This place is a hidden gem. It's not crowded. We are going to return soon!
A phenomenal landscape and well-kept place all right for all visitors in native Florence

Kayaking (rentals)  in the light waves was an experience and not that hard.   Great beach with relatively shallow for long distances.   Less than a foot for a while 5 or so feet deep at max.   Awesome picnic areas.  Clean changing and bath rooms...outdoor showers and decent snack shack.

Superb park, has everything you could want in an outdoor experience. The water does not get too warm in Vt, but you can't complain about that. Clean facilities and a nice snack bar. Bring your sand umbrella.

Definitely one of the nicest visitor centers I've seen! There are some really beautiful art pieces by local artists in the main lobby, a gift shop, free coffee, and as you would imagine, a ton of information on what to do in and around Lake Charles. The staff was super friendly and helpful. They pointed us to a splash pad and kids park just a mile down the road which is open to the public, because we were looking for a place to give our kids a break from the road trip. Thanks so much!

One of the nicest visitor centers I have been to by far! Definitely a place to stop. They have an AMAZING selection of pamphlets, lots of seating, and outdoor trail, cool sculptures, and really clean bathrooms. 

I was pleasantly surprised. This would be a great place to stop for lunch or just to take a break.
Very helpful and kind staff, set in a beautiful area. Worth the visit
Great little stop on a trip, clean bathrooms, beautiful scenery. Baby Gators can be viewed just to the left of the building. Recommend if you want to stretch your legs.

It is a great place to stop and take pictures. They have a gift shop and outside of the center there is a swamp structure; inside of it is a baby alligator and turtles. You can swim in the water right outside of center too! Inside the people are helpful and they have tons of flyers to show you what is what in Louisiana or what to do in Louisiana!

Such a great park. Wonderfully updated. But also kept the other playground so two areas for kids to run and play between. It is in a great, safe and quiet location. It is carved out of the surrounding landscape and the walking path that circles the property is a breath of fresh air. The new playground also has an app that you can download for free. You can play games, scavenger hunts, etc. which makes a regular day at the park more fun.
Need small bbq grills for snacks and more lighting for hours after 6 pm it was very dark.  It was very quite and relaxing.
2 playgrounds and a bug swing set! Daughter loved it here
A good place for families or when you need some quiet time alone.
Great place to go walking. Great location and great place to have birthday parties too.

This is an amazing state park. They are constantly adding things to make it even better. They have a very well maintained hiking/biking trail system that is perfect for a beginner in either sport. They have two camping areas, with one being renovated, and several nice cabins you can rent. If you come during the summer and there is plenty of water in the bayou in the middle of the park there's a good chance you'll see some alligators.

We camped here the first part of April. Had a very pleasant time. The campground was not full during the week and was quiet. Still a little cold for fishing and picnicking so not many people. The trails were nice, the disc golf was fun, but could have been marked better from hole to next tee. The showers were older, with push button on. I hate those. There was a super friendly stray kitten running around, which was cute, but drive some of the dogs crazy. We had a pleasant time during our stay. I think the park would be very different during the prime season.

Large RV sites but they are spaced a little close. Couple nice walking trails. Very nice disk golf course. Cabins look nice enough but didn't go in one. River access including a boat ramp. Overall a very nice place for a short stay.

Great, little park. I wish we had full hookups but that's more for just convenience. The park is kept up well. The site was easy to get in to. There are 2 playgrounds and an amazing kids trail. My kids (6 and 3) love the kids trail and we've gone on it every day we've been here. I love the cute cutouts and the animal facts. We've seen lots of real turtles too. We have not seen any alligators, and I'm ok with that!! :) Bathrooms are clean, water is hot. All the park staff are super friendly. No complaints from us!

Wonderful park! I go here very often to take a walk and to take in nature. It’s a great place to relax and enjoy the views or you can adventure down the trails. The orange trail is great for a short walk, and the blue trail is for those who want exercise

Best Mexican food in lake Charles, consistently great. Every now and then a place will open up and have good food then you go back a second time and quality drops but not cancun. Been going there for 15 years and I'm never disappointed. Sometimes we'll share a Nacho's Cancun for an appetizer and it's so good I'll get it as my meal. Thanks for all the great lunch, dinner, and even birthday meals and making me feel like family when I come in.
If you ever hungry for Mexican food, this is the best place to eat... everyone is very friendly there too.. love Cancun Mexican restaurant...
The food was soooo scrumptious & waiters were so nice! Definitely reccomend this place. 😋
Service was good. Food was alright. Not the most authentic I've had and the parking lot SUCKS

Has been our favorite place for quite a while. Food is always very good, service is usually pretty on point, and atmosphere is up to par. Parking lot is limited and kind of tight. Always a good experience here though!

Tony's Pizza is a favorite local hangout. It operates in the original building opened in the 60's. The decor is retro, atmosphere is friendly and relaxing. The pizza is so delicious, many different topping of your choice & extra cheesy. They also serve pasta and salads.
You won't regret it!

Great place! This is one of those restaurants that is a favorite of the locals. Great food. Fun, family oriented atmosphere. Good people. If you're looking for a relaxed, friendly dining experience, check out Tony's Pizza!
I've eaten at Tony's before and enjoyed it.  Wanted to try again and it was great again today.  Fresh hot high quality food. Friendly people and fast service.

The staff was very nice and attentive to refilling drinks. Also the guys taking orders were polite and quick. We tried the Keto pizza with the cauliflower crust, it was extremely good and couldn't tell the difference in the crust. (You can get the cauliflower crust on any of their pizzas). It's a MUST TRY!

Went in here on a Sunday night and it was PACKED so we decided to come back the next day. I'm glad we did. Great Pizza and sandwiches. We got a meats pizza, an Italian sub and a Club Sub. Pizza was great and the subs were meaty and good. Great and fast service. Would come back when we are in the area!

I took my wife here as one of many stops for our 5 year anniversary while in town and it did not disappoint. We went around 7 on a weekday after Valentine's Day and I will admit I was a little nervous about my choice as the restaurant was pretty empty when I went in, but the food was excellent my waiter was great, the decor and Lighting in the room made for a very intimate experience and we greatly enjoyed it! My only advice would be to make sure and slow down while you're on the service road or you might miss it. Even after I had pulled in I wasn't sure if it was a restaurant or a business of some other kind. We decided to split a steak and a seafood plate, it was fantastic. Thanks for the Memories
Quiet, dim, cozy atmosphere. Food had always been perfect. Down home elegant i guess id have to say.
Excellent food & service (wonderful server, Reagan). Wonderful anniversary dinner!  Great steaks!
Good food, but all the seafood is fried on the lunch menu. Good wait staff!

I was part of a party of about 35 so we had a set menu - catfish topped with a crawfish sauce, steak, or grilled chicken topped with some sort of sauce, and all came with a choice of veggies or fries for sides in addition to a salad and choice of dessert (bread pudding or baked fudge). Salad first: standard side salad - lettuce mix and 1 grape tomato. Main course: I had the catfish - well cooked and tasty - with veggies which were your standard frozen, out-of-the-bag with a bechamel-type sauce. Those around me who had the steak or chicken said that you got caught tastes of lighter fluid in addition to over-char on both and I also heard the sauce on the chicken was a bit salty. Dessert: both adequate but left something to be desired. The bread pudding (which does have raisins) had no texture; it was quite literally mushy bread with a hint of cinnamon compacted into a pan and baked. The baked fudge was strange. A hybrid of fudge and cake, it was lacking a rich chocolate flavor that I expected, but in fact so does much fudge. It works have been better served as a smaller portion with a scoop of ice cream. All in all for the price and the hype of the place I was sorely disappointed and will not be returning. I am a transplant to the area and thus did not grow up eating around here; it's certainly true that your taste buds like that to which they are accustomed.
Dark - Quite, But friendly environment. Small cubicle compared to some slot machine casinos. Fast friendly service.
I enjoy going here-i never win...but its a Comfortable little Get Away. The staff are Always Great!
Good gaming environment, and the people who work there are friendly and helpful.

i like kings palace but sometimes the service is slow.  there is a public bathroom. also an atm.  i wish they would update the new games there. plenty of parking.
there is security that watches when you leave. easy to drive to .
restarant in the same building and free cokes and coffee in the casino.

An amazing place to visit. For a night out on the town. And a chance to win a little bit at the same time. For a minimum of a dollar you can win up to $700.00
Playing nickels on fish fry and take a shot.
Hit that multiplier and you got a good chance.
Have fun guys.

I am so pleased that my husband and I decided to try Pujo St Cafe. My new favorite. There were so many menu options it was hard to choose. But we went with the red snapper and stuffed shrimp. Both were delicious. Try the pujo oyster appetizer, you won't be disappointed. They have a full bar and great selection of desserts. Topped it all off with a coffee and bread pudding! Our waiter Kevin was polite, attentive and resourceful. He knew the menu choices and the right questions to ask. Timing was perfect.
It had been a slow time to go which was fine with me. The veggies sandwich was great. Sweet potato fries were good 😋👌👍

Service was terrible. Literally sat most of the time waiting for my server to return so I can ask for things. I enjoyed my coconut shrimp as always. Never experienced bad service to this degree here before. Felt as if my waiter forgot I was even there.

We hosted a Bridal shower at Pujo St. Cafe. The staff made planning quite easy. On the day of the shower the room was set up nicely and the food was delicious. But, the waitress was not at all friendly. When anybody would ask her for water (which should have been out anyways) or coffee, she seemed annoyed. But, overall we were pleased and satisified with Pujo Street Cafe.

Food is good but expensive for what you get.  I ordered Chicken Mykonos and it was delicious. However, for $18.50 I expected a bit more than 5 pieces of chicken. 
The service and atmosphere were wonderful and I would go back (and soon) if it weren't for the prices.

Loved it and my hubby did too! Generous portions of perfectly fried fish for the hubby and a small seafood platter for myself. Both came with too many fries to eat at one sitting and a freshly made salad with baby tomatoes, radish, purple cabbage and crunchy lettuce. If you order the large fish or small seafood platter, it's really 2 meals in one. I can't wait to try the gumbo! And the service was fast, price reasonable and friendly

Love the laid back atmosphere. Perfect for a group or by yourself. The servers were friendly and knowledgeable. The fish was the best I have ever had. And I have had a lot if good fish. Awesome sweet tea too.

I brought my mother and sister for a treat to eat out. My sister just had a birthday!  The food and service was wonderful. Fried shrimp and french fries are very tasty.  The seafood gumbo is good also.

Great place for cajun style seafood. We had boiled crabs that were well seasoned and cooked to perfection, you know it is cooked right when you can crack the claws and crab meat falls out. Incredibly tasty morsels of crab meat. Our group had a business meeting at Seafood Palace. It is a place large enough to accommodate your family for just a meal or party. Food is wonderful. I ate the combo of fried shrimp/fried oysters.
Always a 5 star review. Everyone there works hard to ensure customer satisfaction, from the owner to the bus persons. They take great pride in their work and you can taste it. :)

Good and fresh, but greasy. Registers were down when we went, so ordering took forever. Nice staff. Lots of seafood options. Funky and fun atmosphere, but needs a deep clean. Good for groups and families. Dessert options of cake, cheesecake, pralines, ginger planks, and fruit hand pies.

Everything was so good! Came out fresh and hot! We were very impressed by the whole experience. The staff was very polite and helpful. The servers were all the to help each other out. We will definitely visit again!

One of the best local spots! Truly one of those restaurants that you go to when you're from out of town. It has local flair and fanfare. Fresh seafood, served up all different ways. Don't worry, there is more than just seafood. In my opinion, best gumbo and pistolettes. Easygoing cuisine and atmosphere, why wouldn't you want to go here!

This place is amazing! The staff are on point, friendly, quickly get things done and work as a team. Tiffany was our waiter. She took really good care of us. We are from Houston but we often travel to Louisiana so we will most likely be back for more of the service and the great food. Thank you for a good time.

Absolutely delicious!  Yummy in my tummy!  My server was Carmen and she was awesome!  Acne went above and beyond her duties!  She even showed me how to eat crawfish since it was my first time.   I will definitely be back... very soon!

As always, service and food were excellent! It had been awhile since we've been to Five Points and specifically to Yesterday's; we found a new menu but  they have retained a lot of our favorites. The Chicken Fried Steak (formerly known as Confederate Fried Steak) still remains our favorite. I would not, however, recommend the guacamole... one sad note on an otherwise lovely lunch!

Our waiter was polite and respectful. He also was very attentive. 
I have eaten at Yesterday's before and today had the meatloaf, squash casserole and broccoli as my sides,but the "taste' was different. The meatloaf and squash tasted the same. Go figure.......
Anyhow,this experience will not deter me from visiting again.Unless it happens again.😊

Nice cozy place with a country inspired menu. Lots of tasty sounding option coupled with a good selection of local beers. Servers were all friendly and lively. Parking can be a bit of a bear, but at least you can walk through the quaint downtown area.

One of the oldest businesses in columbia. Great people and great food. It doesn't get much better. Convenient parking and a great family and sports atmosphere. Bar area and dining room have room to accommodate any crowd. You won't be disappointed.
The Cobb Salad is fabulous and huge. I can never finish 😋. Today our waiter was Ellison; she is the best waitress that I have ever met. Great experience 👍
